'''Ritscher Peak''' is a prominent peak (2,790 meters), standing 7 mi WSW of [[Mount Mentzel]] in the [[Gruber Mountains]] of [[Queen Maud Land]]. This peak was discovered and mapped by the [[Third German Antarctic Expedition]] of 1938-39 and was named for Capt. [[Alfred Ritscher]], leader of the expedition.<ref>[http://geonames.usgs.gov/pls/gnispublic/ USGS GNIS: Ritscher Peak]</ref>
